    "title": "Sample Metadata Conventions",
    "content": "Sample Metadata Conventions\n\nStatus of this Convention\n\nThis document provides guidelines for annotating general sample metadata in SDRF-Proteomics format. These conventions apply to samples from any organism (human, animal, plant).\n\nVersion 1.0.0 - 2025-01\n\nAbstract\n\nSample metadata conventions define standardized formats for common properties that apply across all organism types. This convention covers:\n\n- Organism annotation\n- Organism part / tissue annotation\n- Age and temporal information\n- Biological sex\n- Disease and health status\n- Developmental stage\n- Cell type annotation\n\nFor human-specific metadata (disease staging, comorbidities, treatment history, demographics, lifestyle factors), see Human Sample Metadata Convention.\n\nOrganism Annotation\n\nColumn\n\ncharacteristics[organism]\n\nOntology\n\n- Primary: NCBI Taxonomy (NCBITaxon)\n- Alternative: EFO\n\nFormat\n\nUse the scientific name in lowercase:\n\nValue |NCBITaxon ID |Description\n\nhomo sapiens\nNCBITaxon:9606\nHuman\n\nmus musculus\nNCBITaxon:10090\nMouse\n\nrattus norvegicus\nNCBITaxon:10116\nRat\n\ndanio rerio\nNCBITaxon:7955\nZebrafish\n\ndrosophila melanogaster\nNCBITaxon:7227\nFruit fly\n\ncaenorhabditis elegans\nNCBITaxon:6239\nNematode worm\n\nsaccharomyces cerevisiae\nNCBITaxon:4932\nBaker's yeast\n\narabidopsis thaliana\nNCBITaxon:3702\nThale cress\n\n Use lowercase for organism names. The validator will map to the correct ontology term.\n\nOrganism Part / Tissue Annotation\n\nColumn\n\ncharacteristics[organism part]\n\nOntologies\n\nOrganism Type |Ontology |URL\n\nMammals/Vertebrates\nUBERON\n\nPlants\nPlant Ontology (PO)\n\nDrosophila\nFlyBase Anatomy (FBbt)\n\nC. elegans\nWormBase Anatomy (WBbt)\n\nCommon Values\n\nValue |UBERON ID |Description\n\nblood\nUBERON:0000178\nWhole blood\n\nblood plasma\nUBERON:0001969\nPlasma fraction\n\nblood serum\nUBERON:0001977\nSerum fraction\n\nliver\nUBERON:0002107\nLiver tissue\n\nbrain\nUBERON:0000955\nBrain tissue\n\nheart\nUBERON:0000948\nHeart tissue\n\nkidney\nUBERON:0002113\nKidney tissue\n\nlung\nUBERON:0002048\nLung tissue\n\nskin\nUBERON:0002097\nSk",
